{"lemma": "ثَيِّبٌ", "slug": "ثَيِّبٌ", "root": "ث.#.ب", "root_slug": "ث-_-ب", "root_link": "/words/roots/ث-_-ب", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 3}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n4807"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%90%D9%91%D8%A8%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "married person", "fa": "شوهردیده", "ur": "شوهردار", "tr": "evli kimse", "id": "orang yang pernah menikah", "bn": "বিবাহিত ব্যক্তি", "es": "persona casada", "fr": "personne mariée", "de": "verheiratete Person", "ru": "бывшая в браке", "zh": "已婚者"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a man or woman who has ever been married; not a virgin", "examples": [{"text": "تَائِبَاتٍ عَابِدَاتٍ سَائِحَاتٍ ثَيِّبَاتٍ وَأَبْكَارًا", "english": "repentant, dedicated to worship and fasting—previously married or virgins."}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a woman who is divorced or widowed"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "some gramineous plant"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/θaj.jib/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n4807", "headword_ar": "ثَيِّبٌ", "root": "vwb", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", [like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "say~idN", "text_ar": "سَيِّدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; originally"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vawiybN", "text_ar": "ثَوِيبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vayowibN", "text_ar": "ثَيْوِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; i. e.] of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faEiylN", "text_ar": "فَعِيلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Mgh,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fayoEilN", "text_ar": "فَيْعِلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Msb;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A woman who has become separated from her husband"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, T, M, Mgh, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in any manner:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, T, M, Mgh:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a woman whose husband has died,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who has been divorced, and has then returned to the marriage-state:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AHeyth, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one that is not a virgin:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAth, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a woman to whom a man has gone in;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a man who has gone in to a woman:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ks, ISk, S, Mgh, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a person who has married:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a man"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a woman;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, S, M, Msb;) like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bikorN", "text_ar": "بِكْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ay~imN", "text_ar": "اَيِّمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Mgh, Msb:) from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vaAba", "text_ar": "ثَابَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (IAth, Mgh, Msb;) because they generally return time after time to the marriage-state: (Mgh:) but mostly applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a woman;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because she returns to her family in a manner different from the first [state]; (Msb;) or because the suitors return to her time after time: (Mgh:) or it is not applied to a man (Lth, El-'Eyn, T, M, Mgh, K) except in the dual form, as when one says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waladu Alv~ay~ibayoni", "text_ar": "وَلَدُ الثَّيِّبَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Lth, El-'Eyn, T, M, K:) and a woman is also termed ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muvay~ibN", "text_ar": "مُثَيِّبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (M;) or ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muvay~abN", "text_ar": "مُثَيَّبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muEaZamN", "text_ar": "مُعَظَمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K: [but see 2, last sentence but two:]) the pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vayibN", "text_ar": "ثَيِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "applied to a woman is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vay~ibaAtN", "text_ar": "ثَيِّبَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, Mgh, Msb,) and the post-classical writers say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vuy~abN", "text_ar": "ثُيَّبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which has not been heard as genuine Arabic: (Mgh, * Msb:) its pl. if applied to a man is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vuy~ibuwna", "text_ar": "ثُيِّبُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.) It is said in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alv~ay~ibaAni yurojamaAni waAlbikoraAni yujoladaAni wayugar~abaAni", "text_ar": "الثَّيِّبَانِ يُرْجَمَانِ وَالبِكْرَانِ يُجْلَدَانِ وَيُغَرَّبَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The two persons of whom each has previously had carnal intercourse in marriage with one of the other sex shall be stoned"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "if they commit adultery together;"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and the two who have previously had no connubial intercourse with others shall be flogged and banished"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "if they commit fornication together]. (T.) ―         -b2-  It is also applied to (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A woman who has attained the age of puberty, though a a virgin;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "tropically, and by extension of its proper signification. (IAth, TA.) ―         -b3-  This word is mentioned in the K [and M] in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vyb", "text_ar": "ثيب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and its mention in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vwb", "text_ar": "ثوب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is said by the author of the K to be wrong: but IAth and many others decisively assert that it is from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vaAba", "text_ar": "ثَابَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yavuwbu", "text_ar": "يَثُوبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", “ he returned. ” (MF, TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["Mgh", "Lth", "T", "M", "K", "AHeyth", "TA", "IAth", "Ks", "ISk", "S", "Msb"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}